text: Ch is a digraph in the Latin alphabet, which is made of the consonant letters C and H. It is used in multiple Latin languages including English. ==Languages== Some languages use the digraph Ch in words like in “chào” (hello in Vietnamese), “cheval” (horse in French), “charta” (paper in Latin), “chequear” ("check" in Spanish) and chair in English. ==Related pages== *Th (digraph) ==References== Category:Latin alphabet
title: Ch (digraph)
